  "texts": [
    "Future work must be geared toward improving the state of evaluation to ensure that safety and accuracy remain at the forefront of improvement using generative AI in the clinical domain.In conclusion, we introduced a human evaluation framework specifically designed to assess the key components of diagnosis generation relevant to diagnostic decision support systems, and we have shed light on the misalignment between human evaluations and automated metrics.",
    "Our framework prioritizes diagnostic safety and evidence-based reasoning, ensuring a thorough evaluation of diagnostic generation.",
    "We also focused on achieving a high degree of inter-annotator agreement.",
    "Our findings indicate that the automated metrics currently employed for this task fall short of expectations, as they fail to mirror human judgment accurately.",
    "However, we observed a notable improvement in UMLS-based approaches, attributed to their sophisticated representation of medical knowledge and their foundation in the extensive resources of the National Library of Medicine."
  ],
